It appears that you&#39;re using an H1 version from some of your text.

How this should be configured depends on the site where it must be 
triggered.

Have you examined the target site&#39;s form to confirm all the form values 
necessary to login? (Have you watched a successful login in a web 
browser using a tool that lets you see the form values submitted, like 
Firebug?)

It should not be necessary to edit the order.xml directly -- it should 
be possible to set up the credentials and triggering URLs via the web 
interface. But, it would also be OK to edit the order.xml directly, if 
done properly and before launching Heritrix.

I suggest you look at the AuthSelfTest files in the source distribution 
to see an example of proper configuration and the kind of web-login(s) 
it works against. Relevant files are:

  src/conf/selftest/order.xml
  src/java/org/archive/crawler/selftest/AuthSelfTest.java
  src/webapps/selftest/Auth (and its contents)

- Gordon @ IA

